docs.abstract: Mr. Moonves made his name as a programmer of shows with clear-cut villains and heroes. On Sunday, after more allegations of sexual misconduct, his career was in free fall.
docs.snippet: Mr. Moonves made his name as a programmer of shows with clear-cut villains and heroes. On Sunday, after more allegations of sexual misconduct, his career was in free fall.
docs.lead_paragraph: Leslie Moonves had a strong idea of what a network television program should be. He liked his sitcoms broad, with larger-than-life characters and big laughs. The dramas he selected featured protagonists who scored a win before the credits rolled.

headline.main: Les Moonves Put CBS on Top. Then It All Came Crashing Down.

docs.abstract: Twitter struggled, and failed, to answer the question of what is allowed on its platform. And Elon Musk dealt with the consequences of having tweeted in the first place.
docs.snippet: Twitter struggled, and failed, to answer the question of what is allowed on its platform. And Elon Musk dealt with the consequences of having tweeted in the first place.
docs.lead_paragraph: Each week, technology reporters and columnists from The New York Times review the week’s news, offering analysis and maybe a joke or two about the most important developments in the tech industry.

headline.main: The Week in Tech: When to Tweet
headline.print_headline: Should a Provocateur Be Barred From Twitter? Should Tesla’s Chief Swear It Off?

docs.abstract: Activists became entangled with fake accounts and pages on Facebook, leading to significant consequences for them as the company tried to clamp down.
docs.snippet: Activists became entangled with fake accounts and pages on Facebook, leading to significant consequences for them as the company tried to clamp down.
docs.lead_paragraph: In late June, after word emerged that the white supremacists who organized last year’s deadly “Unite the Right” march in Charlottesville, Va., had applied to hold an anniversary rally this month in Washington, a local political activist, Brendan Orsinger, saw that a Facebook event page had been created for a counterprotest.

headline.main: How Fake Influence Campaigns on Facebook Lured Real People
headline.print_headline: Facebook Scrubs Fakers, but Hurts Real Activists

docs.abstract: Alex Stamos, Facebook’s chief security officer, is joining Stanford to teach and to examine the role of security and technology in society.

docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — When Facebook revealed on Tuesday that it had identified a political influence campaign ahead of the November midterm elections, the company’s chief security officer, Alex Stamos, was front-and-center in speaking on the issue.

headline.main: Facebook’s Security Chief to Depart for Stanford University
